# Environment Setup Guide
# 
# Copy to .env.local for your personal secrets (API keys, database URLs)
# Copy to .env for shared default values (can be committed)
#
# .env.local (NEVER commit - contains your secrets)
# .env (CAN commit - contains safe defaults)

# Database Connection (Required for production, optional for local dev)
# Add to .env.local: DATABASE_URL=postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/neondb?sslmode=require
# Get your connection string from Neon dashboard: https://console.neon.tech

# Session Security (Required for authentication)
# Add to .env.local: SESSION_SECRET=your-random-secret-key-for-sessions
# Or use default from .env for development

# AI Configuration (Required for chat functionality)
# Add to .env.local: GROQ_API_KEY=your-groq-api-key-here
# Get your free API key at: https://console.groq.com/keys

# Default Model (can stay in .env)
GROQ_MODEL=llama-3.1-8b-instant

# Note: This app uses a custom authentication system (not NextAuth.js)
# - .env.local: Your personal secrets (API keys, database URLs) - NEVER commit
# - .env: Safe defaults and shared config - CAN commit
# - For local development: Works without DATABASE_URL (uses in-memory storage)
# - For production: DATABASE_URL and GROQ_API_KEY required in .env.local
